article.headline: Wyoming 73, Louisiana Tech 58
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Luke Martinez scored a career-high 20 points to lead Wyoming to the championship of the Jim Thorpe Classic with a 73-58 win over Louisiana Tech on Sunday night. Martinez was named MVP after going 13 of 21 from beyond the arc and averaging 17.0 points during the round-robin event. Francisco Cruz added 18 points and Adam Waddell 11 for the Cowboys (6-1). Cordarius Johnson led the Bulldogs (2-3) with 16 points while Kenyon McNeail scored 13 and Romario Souza 10. Martinez sank three of his five 3s in the first period to help Wyoming to a 31-23 halftime lead. A rare 3-pointer by Leonard Washington put the Cowboys up 39-23 and the margin ranged from 10 to 23 the rest of the way. Wyoming was 3-0 in the tournament, Portland State 2-1, Louisiana Tech 1-2 and Maryland-Eastern Shore 0-3.
